<title>JAPAN: Pace of yen rise too rapid - MOF's Sakakibara.</title>
<headline>Pace of yen rise too rapid - MOF's Sakakibara.</headline>
<dateline>TOKYO 1997-05-20</dateline>
<text>
<p>Japan's &quot;Mr Yen&quot;, Eisuke Sakakibara, told Reuters on Tuesday that the pace of the yen's strengthening against the dollar was too rapid.</p>
<p>&quot;The pace of the yen's strengthening is too rapid,&quot; said Sakakibara, the director-general of the Finance Ministry's International Finance Bureau.</p>
<p>He added that too much volatility in foreign exchange markets was undesirable and that Japan would &quot;deal appropriately&quot; with such excessive volatility.</p>
</text>
